## Description {#details}

The data structure for the dependency graph.

Note that in this graph if there is an edge from A to B (A -&gt; B), then it means that B depends on A, and when the state of A is updated, node B should also be updated

Definition at line 550 of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/transforms/include/llvm/transforms/ipo/attributor-h">Attributor.h</a>.

## Public Member Attributes

### SyntheticRoot {#a79dfbbbabebeb796bff8a6a998840aba}

<MemberDefinition
  prototype="AADepGraphNode llvm::AADepGraph::SyntheticRoot">
There is no root node for the dependency graph.

But the SCCIterator requires a single entry point, so we maintain a fake(&quot;synthetic&quot;) root node that depends on every node.

Definition at line <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/transforms/include/llvm/transforms/ipo/attributor-h/#l00562">562</a> of file <a href="/docs/api/files/include/include/llvm/include/llvm/transforms/include/llvm/transforms/ipo/attributor-h">Attributor.h</a>.
